This paper is about natural language understanding, specifically the automatic extraction of temporal information from text. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to achieve state-of-the-art performance, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the importance of temporal understanding for information retrieval (cs.IR) and time-aware applications (cs.NE), which further supports these sub-categories as likely options.
